This paper uses Twitter data to analyze the effectiveness of campaign tactics in the 2016 U.S. presidential election. It involves social media analysis, statistical modeling, and data mining techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of social media analysis (cs.SI), data mining (cs.SD), computational social science (cs.CY), social computing (cs.SOC), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
